y><expanded_objects></expanded_objects><topic_dirs><topic_dir><name>Croup</name><link_title>Croup</link_title><description>Croup is a common respiratory  problem in young children. It tends to occur in the fall and winter. Its main symptom is a harsh, barking cough. Croup causes swelling and narrowing in the voice box, windpipe, and breathing tubes that lead to the lungs. This can make it hard for your child to breathe. An attack of croup can be scary, but it is rarely serious. Children usually get better in several days with rest and care at home. Follow the links below to find WebMD's comprehensive coverage about how croup is contracted, what it looks like, how to treat it, and much more.</description><friendly_url>http://www.webmd.com/children/croup-directory</friendly_url></topic_dir><related_assets><asset id="091e9c5e8000dc7e"><link_title>Study Shows Link Between a Virus and Croup</link_title><friendly_url>http://www.webmd.com/news/20050822/study-shows-link-between-virus-croup</friendly_url><thumbnail height="" width="" alt=""></thumbnail><collection_category_val>1005</collection_category_val><archive>1</archive></asset><asset id="091e9c5e8000df72"><link_title>Don't Expose Infants to Coughers, Says CDC</link_title><friendly_url>http://www.webmd.com/parenting/baby/news/20050127/dont-expose-infants-to-coughers-says-cdc</friendly_url><thumbnail height="" width="" alt=""></thumbnail><collection_category_val>1005</collection_category_val><archive>1</archive></asset><asset id="091e9c5e8000c109"><link_title>Do Cough Medicines Work in Kids?</link_title><friendly_url>http://www.webmd.com/cold-and-flu/news/20040706/do-cough-medicines-work-in-kids</friendly_url><thumbnail height="" width="" alt=""></thumbnail><collection_category_val>1005</collection_category_val><archive>1</archive></asset><asset id="091e9c5e800a4281"><link_title>Does Your Baby Have a Breathing Problem?</link_title><friendly_url>http://www.webmd.com/parenting/baby/your-newborn-babys-breathing-noises</fri